    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Debating Global Warming</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John E Colbert letter on December 3 article holds Bush administration is using different standards of proof for possible war with Iraq and global warming</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The Bush administration is prepared to go to war with Iraq with little evidence that Iraq has dangerous weapons that threaten the United States (''Can Global Warming Be Studied Too Much?'' Dec. 3), yet when it comes to warming and the environment, this administration will wait indefinitely before acting. Certainly, different standards of proof are being applied.</p>
        <p>JOHN E. COLBERT  Chicago</p>
      </block>
